1
00:00:19,760 --> 00:00:20,600
Madam Su,

2
00:00:20,839 --> 00:00:22,160
it's not that I won't give you the medicine.

3
00:00:22,480 --> 00:00:23,960
It's just that this disease is very severe.

4
00:00:24,600 --> 00:00:24,879
Look,

5
00:00:25,039 --> 00:00:26,760
we've run out of medicine in our stock.

6
00:00:27,359 --> 00:00:28,160
What should we do now?

7
00:00:28,519 --> 00:00:29,600
The medicine shops outside

8
00:00:29,600 --> 00:00:31,239
have tripled their prices.

9
00:00:31,559 --> 00:00:33,479
The Women's clinic can't afford it.

10
00:00:34,079 --> 00:00:34,560
How about this,

11
00:00:35,240 --> 00:00:36,920
I'll try to set aside some for you.

12
00:00:37,200 --> 00:00:37,920
If you can

13
00:00:38,039 --> 00:00:39,840
get the merchants to bring in supplies,

14
00:00:40,320 --> 00:00:42,079
I'll send some to you then.

15
00:00:42,399 --> 00:00:42,840
Alright.

16
00:00:43,520 --> 00:00:44,039
Thank you.

17
00:00:44,280 --> 00:00:45,079
Go back now.

18
00:00:49,479 --> 00:00:50,240
Sir,

19
00:00:50,679 --> 00:00:52,159
please get me two doses of medicine for diarrhea.

20
00:00:52,479 --> 00:00:54,280
My husband is dying.

21
00:00:54,479 --> 00:00:55,119
Please.

22
00:00:55,119 --> 00:00:55,560
Ma'am.

23
00:00:55,719 --> 00:00:56,479
Everyone,

24
00:00:56,960 --> 00:00:59,240
we've run out of medicine.

25
00:00:59,600 --> 00:01:00,679
The fire for decoction

26
00:01:01,039 --> 00:01:02,280
has never stopped.

27
00:01:02,799 --> 00:01:05,120
If you can't bear the pain,

28
00:01:05,599 --> 00:01:08,359
you can go to the Women's Clinic.

29
00:01:08,799 --> 00:01:09,439
Ridiculous!

30
00:01:09,680 --> 00:01:11,719
That's for women's diseases.

31
00:01:11,959 --> 00:01:13,480
What can we men do there?

32
00:01:13,599 --> 00:01:14,920
The epidemic knows no gender or age.

33
00:01:15,280 --> 00:01:16,079
It's all about the symptoms.

34
00:01:17,120 --> 00:01:17,560
We won't go.

35
00:01:18,560 --> 00:01:19,599
It's a waste of time.

36
00:01:20,480 --> 00:01:21,599
How can we trust female doctors?

37
00:01:22,239 --> 00:01:23,519
We'd rather wait here for medicine.

38
00:01:24,920 --> 00:01:25,719
Look at you.

39
00:01:26,359 --> 00:01:27,599
The epidemic is fierce today,

40
00:01:27,959 --> 00:01:29,079
and has already taken many lives.

41
00:01:29,200 --> 00:01:30,200
If we continue to hold onto prejudices

42
00:01:30,439 --> 00:01:31,439
and reject good doctors,

43
00:01:31,840 --> 00:01:33,040
we may regret it too late.

44
00:01:33,359 --> 00:01:34,239
That's all I have to say.

45
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:35,680
I hope you all

46
00:01:36,359 --> 00:01:36,959
take care.

47
00:01:41,079 --> 00:01:42,480
Twenty years ago, there was a plague in the northwest.

48
00:01:43,359 --> 00:01:44,480
The symptoms were high fever,

49
00:01:44,879 --> 00:01:45,840
watery diarrhea,

50
00:01:46,200 --> 00:01:47,079
vomiting blood, and bloody stool,

51
00:01:47,799 --> 00:01:49,239
exactly like the patients today.

52
00:01:50,079 --> 00:01:50,879
This disease spreads quickly.

53
00:01:51,480 --> 00:01:52,480
If it's not controlled within three days,

54
00:01:53,799 --> 00:01:55,079
it could spread throughout the city.

55
00:01:56,400 --> 00:01:57,640
How was it finally cured?

56
00:01:59,599 --> 00:02:00,920
All the patients were gathered in one place

57
00:02:01,719 --> 00:02:02,640
and quarantined.

58
00:02:03,680 --> 00:02:04,200
In the end,

59
00:02:05,280 --> 00:02:06,560
those who were infected died,

60
00:02:07,239 --> 00:02:07,879
and the epidemic...

61
00:02:10,360 --> 00:02:11,560
So they just let it run its course?

62
00:02:12,759 --> 00:02:13,840
We can't repeat that mistake.

63
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:16,039
Huo Po Xia Ling Decoction

64
00:02:17,039 --> 00:02:18,000
can clear damp-heat,

65
00:02:18,719 --> 00:02:19,479
and the Ma Xing Shi Gan Decoction

66
00:02:20,039 --> 00:02:20,759
can dispel lung heat.

67
00:02:21,439 --> 00:02:23,319
But these are all symptomatic treatments.

68
00:02:23,879 --> 00:02:25,280
We need to find the source of the infection.

69
00:02:28,560 --> 00:02:29,599
I just went to inquire at the alley entrance.

70
00:02:30,240 --> 00:02:31,560
The grain shop owner from the East Market

71
00:02:31,960 --> 00:02:33,240
and the seamstress from the West Market

72
00:02:33,719 --> 00:02:35,159
both started showing symptoms yesterday.

73
00:02:36,400 --> 00:02:37,199
They all said

74
00:02:38,039 --> 00:02:39,479
They drank southern water days ago.

75
00:02:40,400 --> 00:02:42,080
I brought some over with a wet cloth.

76
00:02:50,639 --> 00:02:51,639
It has a pungent, decaying odor.

77
00:02:52,039 --> 00:02:53,120
The smell is too mixed

78
00:02:53,520 --> 00:02:54,240
to identify the source.

79
00:02:58,479 --> 00:02:59,759
Our stock of herbs is running low.

80
00:03:00,199 --> 00:03:02,080
I just sent someone to the herb shops,

81
00:03:02,800 --> 00:03:05,080
and they said the prices have tripled.

82
00:03:05,719 --> 00:03:07,639
We can't borrow much from Ren'an Hall.

83
00:03:09,120 --> 00:03:10,080
We must buy them even if the prices have risen.

84
00:03:10,759 --> 00:03:11,280
Sister Su,

85
00:03:12,960 --> 00:03:14,039
go ask those shops

86
00:03:14,560 --> 00:03:16,280
if we can get some herbs on credit.

87
00:03:16,680 --> 00:03:17,759
We'll repay them double

88
00:03:17,879 --> 00:03:18,759
once the epidemic is over.

89
00:03:20,520 --> 00:03:21,120
Yan Ge,

90
00:03:21,919 --> 00:03:22,800
besides the water source,

91
00:03:23,639 --> 00:03:24,719
find out where

92
00:03:25,199 --> 00:03:26,400
the patients have been

93
00:03:26,400 --> 00:03:27,439
and what they've been in contact with.

94
00:03:27,879 --> 00:03:28,719
We must find the source.

95
00:03:29,360 --> 00:03:29,719
Yes.

96
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:31,719
Be careful.

97
00:03:32,240 --> 00:03:32,639
Yes.

98
00:03:33,280 --> 00:03:33,960
We'll go now.

99
00:03:53,400 --> 00:03:54,639
Folks,

100
00:03:55,360 --> 00:03:56,639
those who haven't been infected

101
00:03:56,639 --> 00:03:58,840
can each take a preventive pill.

102
00:03:59,400 --> 00:04:00,759
Take one every morning.

103
00:04:02,280 --> 00:04:04,400
Will this really protect us from the disease?

104
00:04:04,560 --> 00:04:05,719
It's just to boost your immunity,

105
00:04:05,879 --> 00:04:06,800
not a guarantee

106
00:04:07,039 --> 00:04:08,520
against infection.

107
00:04:09,120 --> 00:04:10,000
Then why bother taking it?

108
00:04:10,560 --> 00:04:11,400
It's free,

109
00:04:11,719 --> 00:04:12,840
what if it kills someone?

110
00:04:13,520 --> 00:04:14,240
Forget it.

111
00:04:18,120 --> 00:04:19,120
People are naturally

112
00:04:20,360 --> 00:04:21,120
fearful in such times.

113
00:04:27,240 --> 00:04:29,319
The West Market has been closed for three days,

114
00:04:29,600 --> 00:04:31,759
and the number of cases in the city is rising daily.

115
00:04:32,160 --> 00:04:33,879
Many have already died from the illness,

116
00:04:34,279 --> 00:04:35,959
and some are trying to flee the city,

117
00:04:36,240 --> 00:04:37,879
but the gates are guarded

118
00:04:38,199 --> 00:04:39,000
to control entry and exit.

119
00:04:39,240 --> 00:04:40,160
Our medicine convoy

120
00:04:40,399 --> 00:04:41,480
is also stuck outside the city.

121
00:04:41,639 --> 00:04:42,120
A'Nong,

122
00:04:42,639 --> 00:04:43,600
come with me to discuss with

123
00:04:43,800 --> 00:04:44,639
the Capital Prefecture and the Guild.

124
00:04:49,560 --> 00:04:49,920
Give us some medicine.

125
00:04:49,920 --> 00:04:50,879
We really have run out of medicine.

126
00:04:51,079 --> 00:04:51,879
Go away.

127
00:04:56,240 --> 00:04:56,879
Sir,

128
00:04:57,040 --> 00:04:57,720
don't be afraid.

129
00:04:57,879 --> 00:04:58,560
They have no medicine,

130
00:04:58,680 --> 00:04:59,360
but we do.

131
00:04:59,800 --> 00:05:00,560
Let me take a look at you.

132
00:05:00,560 --> 00:05:01,680
How can a women's clinic

133
00:05:01,759 --> 00:05:03,519
treat men?

134
00:05:04,319 --> 00:05:05,240
In the face of the epidemic,

135
00:05:05,399 --> 00:05:06,160
life is at stake.

136
00:05:06,360 --> 00:05:07,120
It doesn't matter whether it's a man or a woman.

137
00:05:07,519 --> 00:05:08,680
Forget it.

138
00:05:12,519 --> 00:05:12,959
Sir,

139
00:05:13,439 --> 00:05:14,439
let me treat you.

140
00:05:14,759 --> 00:05:15,600
If you're not at ease,

141
00:05:15,959 --> 00:05:17,279
we have male physicians here too.

142
00:05:17,600 --> 00:05:18,839
Please rest assured.

143
00:05:19,120 --> 00:05:20,600
We will do our utmost.

144
00:05:22,600 --> 00:05:24,040
Then I'll trouble this young master.

145
00:05:26,079 --> 00:05:27,279
The pharmacies and clinics in the city

146
00:05:27,279 --> 00:05:28,160
are all too busy to help,

147
00:05:28,439 --> 00:05:29,519
even turning away patients.

148
00:05:30,279 --> 00:05:31,120
Only we

149
00:05:31,120 --> 00:05:32,439
are still treating patients,

150
00:05:32,959 --> 00:05:34,079
yet so few come.

151
00:05:35,319 --> 00:05:36,360
They must think

152
00:05:37,040 --> 00:05:38,639
a woman-run clinic

153
00:05:39,399 --> 00:05:40,920
would only treat female patients.

154
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:43,120
We can't change

155
00:05:43,480 --> 00:05:44,519
other's prejudices.

156
00:05:46,680 --> 00:05:48,240
We can only do our best

157
00:05:49,160 --> 00:05:50,519
to

158
00:05:51,040 --> 00:05:51,800
live up to our conscience.

159
00:05:55,120 --> 00:05:56,000
Stick out your tongue.

160
00:05:58,519 --> 00:05:59,240
Is anyone here?

161
00:05:59,680 --> 00:06:01,360
Please, help my child!

162
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:03,040
We're closed for the day.

163
00:06:03,480 --> 00:06:04,279
Go somewhere else.

164
00:06:12,519 --> 00:06:13,279
Please!

165
00:06:13,360 --> 00:06:14,040
Open up!

166
00:06:14,240 --> 00:06:15,800
My child is dying!

167
00:06:16,639 --> 00:06:17,480
We're closed for the day.

168
00:06:17,920 --> 00:06:18,959
Come back tomorrow.

169
00:06:30,160 --> 00:06:32,040
Please, save my child!

170
00:06:32,560 --> 00:06:32,879
Quick,

171
00:06:32,959 --> 00:06:33,680
put the child on the bed.

172
00:06:43,600 --> 00:06:44,279
Why did you wait so long

173
00:06:44,279 --> 00:06:45,079
to bring the child here?

174
00:06:46,199 --> 00:06:47,279
He was just

175
00:06:47,279 --> 00:06:48,759
feeling unwell a few days ago.

176
00:06:48,759 --> 00:06:50,759
The clinics are overcrowded,

177
00:06:50,759 --> 00:06:51,879
and we never got a chance.

178
00:06:52,759 --> 00:06:54,720
I had to let him endure it.

179
00:06:54,720 --> 00:06:55,639
Who knew...

180
00:06:56,240 --> 00:06:56,879
Don't cry.

181
00:06:57,279 --> 00:06:58,079
The child can still be saved.

182
00:06:59,120 --> 00:06:59,839
Sister Su,

183
00:07:00,160 --> 00:07:01,279
bring the Qi-boosting pills we made.

184
00:07:04,519 --> 00:07:05,639
You're with the child every day,

185
00:07:06,040 --> 00:07:07,000
so you must also take precautions.

186
00:07:07,360 --> 00:07:08,560
Each family member should take

187
00:07:08,720 --> 00:07:09,839
one pill daily.

188
00:07:11,120 --> 00:07:11,879
Thank you, doctor.

189
00:07:36,480 --> 00:07:37,040
Doctor.

190
00:07:37,519 --> 00:07:38,279
The child is awake.

191
00:07:42,639 --> 00:07:43,000
Here.

192
00:07:44,160 --> 00:07:45,000
Take three doses in a row.

193
00:07:45,680 --> 00:07:46,839
and avoid cold and spicy foods.

194
00:07:47,240 --> 00:07:48,560
Thank you, doctor.

195
00:07:49,199 --> 00:07:50,160
You're truly a saint,

196
00:07:50,240 --> 00:07:51,360
our lifesaver!

197
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:52,639
It's late.

198
00:07:52,879 --> 00:07:54,000
Take the child home.

199
00:07:54,959 --> 00:07:55,480
And remember,

200
00:07:55,680 --> 00:07:56,639
the epidemic is still around.

201
00:07:57,000 --> 00:07:58,079
Cover your mouth and nose.

202
00:07:59,000 --> 00:07:59,360
Thank you.

203
00:08:11,600 --> 00:08:12,879
When the epidemic first broke out,

204
00:08:13,120 --> 00:08:15,079
we stocked up on many herbs in the storage.

205
00:08:15,720 --> 00:08:16,959
If we keep them in the backyard,

206
00:08:17,120 --> 00:08:18,360
they might get infested by pests.

207
00:08:19,079 --> 00:08:20,839
It would be better to transfer them to other clinics.

208
00:08:21,879 --> 00:08:22,240
This way,

209
00:08:22,720 --> 00:08:24,399
we can help those in urgent need

210
00:08:24,800 --> 00:08:26,120
and also exchange them for some silver

211
00:08:26,120 --> 00:08:27,720
to cover our daily expenses.

212
00:08:29,519 --> 00:08:30,160
Sounds good.

213
00:08:31,360 --> 00:08:32,440
No matter which clinic

214
00:08:32,440 --> 00:08:33,679
these herbs end up in,

215
00:08:34,039 --> 00:08:35,360
as long as they help the patients,

216
00:08:35,879 --> 00:08:36,879
they are being put to good use.

217
00:08:37,600 --> 00:08:38,240
Come on, come on.

218
00:08:40,360 --> 00:08:41,159
This is the place.

219
00:08:41,240 --> 00:08:42,000
This is the clinic.

220
00:08:42,639 --> 00:08:43,240
May I ask

221
00:08:43,240 --> 00:08:44,320
what brings you here?

222
00:08:46,159 --> 00:08:47,080
My father said

223
00:08:47,080 --> 00:08:48,399
you can treat the epidemic.

224
00:08:49,120 --> 00:08:49,759
I heard

225
00:08:49,919 --> 00:08:51,679
you cured a child from my neighborhood.

226
00:08:51,759 --> 00:08:53,320
We're also here for treatment.

227
00:08:53,759 --> 00:08:55,559
I thought you were here to make trouble.

228
00:08:56,000 --> 00:08:56,519
No, no, no.

229
00:08:56,600 --> 00:08:57,559
Please stay calm.

230
00:08:57,639 --> 00:08:58,480
Take a seat first.

231
00:08:58,480 --> 00:08:58,799
Come.

232
00:08:59,360 --> 00:08:59,799
Boss.

233
00:09:00,039 --> 00:09:00,600
Madam Yin.

234
00:09:01,240 --> 00:09:01,679
Zhen!

235
00:09:01,879 --> 00:09:02,320
Zhen!

236
00:09:02,480 --> 00:09:02,919
Zhen!

237
00:09:03,080 --> 00:09:03,519
Zhen!

238
00:09:03,639 --> 00:09:04,519
You're infected too?

239
00:09:29,159 --> 00:09:29,720
Why are you vomiting?

240
00:09:30,000 --> 00:09:30,399
Doctor!

241
00:09:31,159 --> 00:09:31,559
Xinyue,

242
00:09:31,919 --> 00:09:32,399
come quickly!

243
00:09:34,840 --> 00:09:35,360
What's going on?

244
00:09:36,039 --> 00:09:37,000
What medicine did they take?

245
00:09:37,240 --> 00:09:38,519
Their condition is quite severe.

246
00:09:38,919 --> 00:09:39,799
We just administered them

247
00:09:39,879 --> 00:09:40,519
Ge Gen Qin Lian Pills.

248
00:09:42,879 --> 00:09:43,639
Do you have any insights?

249
00:09:44,320 --> 00:09:45,039
It seems somewhat different

250
00:09:45,320 --> 00:09:46,279
from the plague.

251
00:09:52,279 --> 00:09:53,279
It is indeed the plague,

252
00:09:53,960 --> 00:09:54,519
but...

253
00:09:55,519 --> 00:09:56,720
I shouldn't have trusted you.

254
00:09:57,080 --> 00:09:58,480
What can this women's clinic treat?

255
00:09:58,559 --> 00:09:59,399
It's better not to treat at all.

256
00:09:59,879 --> 00:10:00,200
Let's go!

257
00:10:03,600 --> 00:10:04,600
Please wait a moment.

258
00:10:05,120 --> 00:10:06,440
The medicine we prescribed was correct.

259
00:10:06,919 --> 00:10:08,000
Now that the epidemic has mutated,

260
00:10:08,000 --> 00:10:08,759
there must be an external cause.

261
00:10:08,960 --> 00:10:10,159
Please allow me to investigate the cause.

262
00:10:10,639 --> 00:10:11,799
I can perform acupuncture first

263
00:10:11,879 --> 00:10:12,639
to control the condition.

264
00:10:12,639 --> 00:10:13,159
Are you mad?

265
00:10:13,759 --> 00:10:15,000
Still talking nonsense here.

266
00:10:15,559 --> 00:10:16,960
My wife is about to vomit blood to death.

267
00:10:17,480 --> 00:10:18,759
and you're saying it's not the medicine's fault?

268
00:10:18,879 --> 00:10:20,240
Do you think we're blind?

269
00:10:20,399 --> 00:10:20,840
Let's go!

270
00:10:20,840 --> 00:10:21,879
Please stay calm.

271
00:10:22,720 --> 00:10:23,519
Let me perform acupuncture first

272
00:10:23,519 --> 00:10:24,559
to stabilize everyone's condition.

273
00:10:24,759 --> 00:10:25,360
Everyone,

274
00:10:26,200 --> 00:10:27,639
I am willing to trust Madam Yin.

275
00:10:28,360 --> 00:10:29,759
She has saved my life twice.

276
00:10:30,120 --> 00:10:31,000
I trust her.

277
00:10:31,519 --> 00:10:33,159
If anyone still has doubts,

278
00:10:33,559 --> 00:10:35,679
I'm willing to let her treat me first.

279
00:10:37,720 --> 00:10:38,240
Yan Ge,

280
00:10:38,440 --> 00:10:38,879
get me the needles.

281
00:10:39,000 --> 00:10:39,240
Coming.

282
00:10:57,679 --> 00:10:59,320
The acupuncture has eased the nausea,

283
00:11:00,200 --> 00:11:02,320
but the pulse remains erratic and weak.

284
00:11:03,000 --> 00:11:03,879
Would you be willing

285
00:11:04,240 --> 00:11:05,519
to stay at the Women's Clinic for a few days?

286
00:11:05,720 --> 00:11:06,639
I'd like to,

287
00:11:07,519 --> 00:11:07,960
but

288
00:11:08,360 --> 00:11:10,320
I have a young child at home to care for.

289
00:11:11,120 --> 00:11:11,879
Besides,

290
00:11:12,600 --> 00:11:13,759
my mother-in-law has just passed away,

291
00:11:14,639 --> 00:11:16,440
and my husband needs to handle the funeral affairs.

292
00:11:17,240 --> 00:11:18,960
I'm worried he can't manage everything alone.

293
00:11:19,279 --> 00:11:20,279
Your mother-in-law just passed away?

294
00:11:20,799 --> 00:11:21,639
Was it due to the epidemic?

295
00:11:25,279 --> 00:11:25,919
Then,

296
00:11:26,279 --> 00:11:27,639
when she passed away,

297
00:11:28,440 --> 00:11:29,639
did she also vomit black blood?

298
00:11:32,080 --> 00:11:32,559
Yes.

299
00:11:33,919 --> 00:11:36,360
And her body also showed some purple spots

300
00:11:37,240 --> 00:11:38,039
and turned black.

301
00:11:38,720 --> 00:11:41,039
The night before she died, she vomited a lot.

302
00:11:42,000 --> 00:11:43,399
Her lower abdomen was swollen like a drum.

303
00:11:44,240 --> 00:11:45,120
I massaged her.

304
00:11:45,519 --> 00:11:46,120
It was very hard.

305
00:11:48,559 --> 00:11:48,960
Yan Ge.

306
00:11:49,360 --> 00:11:50,399
Check if everyone has

307
00:11:50,519 --> 00:11:51,279
any purple spots.

308
00:11:51,360 --> 00:11:51,759
Turned black.

309
00:11:51,919 --> 00:11:52,559
Hard lower abdomen.

310
00:11:56,759 --> 00:11:57,279
There are purple spots.

311
00:11:58,320 --> 00:11:59,000
- Dark... - Xin Yue.

312
00:12:10,879 --> 00:12:11,639
Everyone has them.

313
00:12:12,240 --> 00:12:13,519
- What should we do? - Xin Yue.

314
00:12:14,799 --> 00:12:16,480
Have either of you had a family member pass away

315
00:12:16,639 --> 00:12:17,559
and been kept at home?

316
00:12:18,639 --> 00:12:19,840
My father has been gone for three days.

317
00:12:20,480 --> 00:12:21,720
I intended to properly bury him,

318
00:12:21,720 --> 00:12:22,879
but now,

319
00:12:23,399 --> 00:12:24,720
even the undertakers are avoiding us.

320
00:12:26,600 --> 00:12:27,240
I see.

321
00:12:28,960 --> 00:12:29,559
Everyone,

322
00:12:30,120 --> 00:12:31,879
do you have any unburied family members?

323
00:12:34,120 --> 00:12:34,519
Yes.

324
00:12:35,000 --> 00:12:36,039
I do.

325
00:12:36,879 --> 00:12:37,840
Me too.

326
00:12:38,360 --> 00:12:39,039
If I say

327
00:12:39,559 --> 00:12:40,120
these bodies

328
00:12:40,759 --> 00:12:42,240
must be burned together,

329
00:12:42,879 --> 00:12:43,440
will you agree?

330
00:12:43,720 --> 00:12:44,559
Are you out of your mind?

331
00:12:45,120 --> 00:12:45,720
You can't cure the illness,

332
00:12:45,879 --> 00:12:47,120
so you blame the bodies.

333
00:12:48,200 --> 00:12:49,240
When someone dies,

334
00:12:49,759 --> 00:12:51,159
the body must be kept for three to seven days

335
00:12:51,159 --> 00:12:52,120
to handle the funeral affairs.

336
00:12:52,600 --> 00:12:54,080
To dispose of the bodies so hastily,

337
00:12:54,840 --> 00:12:56,360
and burn all the bodies together?

338
00:12:56,720 --> 00:12:58,039
The ashes will all be mixed together.

339
00:12:58,519 --> 00:13:00,679
How will we explain this to our ancestors?

340
00:13:00,919 --> 00:13:01,879
Exactly!

341
00:13:01,879 --> 00:13:03,120
Everyone, please listen to me!

342
00:13:03,120 --> 00:13:04,000
Listen to me!

343
00:13:04,480 --> 00:13:05,159
Listen to me!

344
00:13:05,639 --> 00:13:07,080
It's precisely because of the corpses

345
00:13:07,519 --> 00:13:08,960
that the plague has spread.

346
00:13:09,600 --> 00:13:10,679
If not dealt with promptly,

347
00:13:11,120 --> 00:13:11,879
one death

348
00:13:12,000 --> 00:13:13,000
will bring ruin to the entire family.

349
00:13:13,240 --> 00:13:14,000
She is right.

350
00:13:14,360 --> 00:13:15,919
Burning the bodies today to halt the plague

351
00:13:16,600 --> 00:13:18,039
is better than risking future generations.

352
00:13:18,320 --> 00:13:19,600
But if we allow the plague to spread

353
00:13:20,039 --> 00:13:21,159
out of a momentary sense of duty,

354
00:13:21,840 --> 00:13:23,039
we would be committing a grave injustice

355
00:13:23,480 --> 00:13:24,440
in the name of filial piety.

356
00:13:24,600 --> 00:13:25,360
What women's clinic?

357
00:13:25,480 --> 00:13:26,360
A bunch of quack doctors.

358
00:13:26,600 --> 00:13:27,519
We shouldn't listen to them.

359
00:13:29,440 --> 00:13:30,120
Everyone, don't leave yet.

360
00:13:31,000 --> 00:13:31,879
Don't rush.

361
00:13:32,120 --> 00:13:32,960
Please stay.

362
00:13:33,559 --> 00:13:34,320
Don't leave yet.

363
00:13:35,000 --> 00:13:35,799
Don't leave yet.

364
00:13:35,919 --> 00:13:36,720
Don't go.

365
00:13:37,159 --> 00:13:37,639
Zhen,

366
00:13:37,879 --> 00:13:38,519
Where are you going?

367
00:13:42,240 --> 00:13:43,279
What should I do, Xin Yue?

368
00:13:43,480 --> 00:13:44,279
Madam Yin,

369
00:13:45,399 --> 00:13:46,799
I believe you mean well,

370
00:13:48,159 --> 00:13:48,639
but

371
00:13:49,600 --> 00:13:50,399
this matter

372
00:13:50,840 --> 00:13:52,240
concerns the dignity of our ancestors.

373
00:13:53,120 --> 00:13:54,360
As a woman,

374
00:13:55,000 --> 00:13:56,399
I truly cannot make the decision.

375
00:13:57,159 --> 00:13:57,879
I'm sorry.

376
00:13:59,279 --> 00:14:00,440
I'm sorry, boss.

377
00:14:05,399 --> 00:14:06,879
People have their own obsessions,

378
00:14:07,519 --> 00:14:08,519
and it's hard for them to wake up.

379
00:14:11,120 --> 00:14:12,600
Since they've made their decision,

380
00:14:14,279 --> 00:14:15,600
they must bear the consequences

381
00:14:15,960 --> 00:14:16,720
of their choices.

382
00:14:19,120 --> 00:14:20,360
Now that I know the root cause,

383
00:14:21,639 --> 00:14:22,840
how can I just sit back and do nothing?

384
00:14:24,240 --> 00:14:25,200
What do you plan to do?

385
00:14:26,440 --> 00:14:27,879
I'll unite the major clinics in the city

386
00:14:28,279 --> 00:14:29,879
to let everyone know the stakes.

387
00:14:30,279 --> 00:14:31,679
If we let this continue,

388
00:14:32,120 --> 00:14:33,519
the plague will never be eradicated.

389
00:14:34,799 --> 00:14:35,440
But most people's

390
00:14:35,480 --> 00:14:36,759
traditional beliefs are deeply rooted.

391
00:14:37,120 --> 00:14:38,240
How could they change easily?

392
00:14:39,000 --> 00:14:40,279
Aren't they afraid of death?

393
00:14:40,600 --> 00:14:42,159
The shackles in people's hearts

394
00:14:42,600 --> 00:14:44,159
can't be broken by just a disease.

395
00:14:49,559 --> 00:14:50,639
Then I'll report it to the authorities.

396
00:14:51,000 --> 00:14:52,000
Even if the world hates me,

397
00:14:52,200 --> 00:14:53,600
I can't turn a blind eye to their lives.

398
00:14:53,799 --> 00:14:54,519
I don't believe

399
00:14:54,960 --> 00:14:56,039
the authorities would turn a blind eye

400
00:14:56,039 --> 00:14:57,360
to the lives of all in Chang'an.
